    "body": "### Problem\n\nCursorMoved event triggered unexpectedly after opening an unfocusable floating window.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create the following `minimal.lua` file:\r\n\r\n    ```lua\r\n\tlocal win_config = {\r\n\t\twidth = 5,\r\n\t\theight = 5,\r\n\t\trow = 1,\r\n\t\tcol = 1,\r\n\t\trelative = \"editor\",\r\n\t\tstyle = \"minimal\",\r\n\t\tfocusable = false,\r\n\t\tnoautocmd = true,\r\n\t\tzindex = 1,\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\tvim.api.nvim_open_win(vim.api.nvim_create_buf(false, true), true, win_config)\r\n\r\n\tvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"CursorMoved\", {\r\n\t\tcallback = function()\r\n\t\t\tprint(\"info: \" .. vim.inspect(info))\r\n\t\tend,\r\n\t})\r\n    ```\r\n\r\n2. `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua`\r\n3. Observe the the autocmd info is printed while it shoudn't. We are only opening an unfocustable window, not jumping into it.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nCursorMoved event should not trigger.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-2074+g786089013d\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim does not have `nvim_open_win`\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux 6.6.9-arch1-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.12.3 (5efb0690) + tmux 3.3a\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nAUR",
