            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "But you are jumping into it by passing `true` as the second argument of `nvim_open_win`, which you can see by sourcing the script after Nvim has started. On startup the reverse happens: the first `CursorMoved` event was defined when you have already jumped into the window, and Nvim moves back to the original window, which triggers the event.",
